flowRoot.flowPara: If you are wanting to make a different set to fit the color scheme of an application, copy this file and save it in your source. Then in Inkscape, go into the fill of one icon (1). You should see "primary" selected (2). Change the color you want (3). Since all the icons are inkscape "swatches", that will change that color everywhere, in all the icons.

These can be re-exported in Inkscape, by selecting them all and then using the PNG Export command with the "Batch export" option ticked. That will use the ID of each object as a file name. Each of these icons has an ID that matches the file name expected by SIL.Windows.Forms.Media.Resources, and is already sized to by 16 px high.
1) Check that they are actually exported at 16px. I found I had to set the height manually in the export box. Once you click "Batch export" that height gets disabled, but it is still used!
2) 2 of the icons (webcam and headset) would not actually show up during a batch export, had to be done separately.
